00:30:39.230 --> 00:30:41.730
I was curious what kind
of zombie questions

00:30:41.730 --> 00:30:42.840
you had for them?

00:30:42.840 --> 00:30:44.364
And were they really helpful?

00:30:44.364 --> 00:30:46.030
MIRA GRANT: They were
extremely helpful.

00:30:46.030 --> 00:30:48.180
I wanted to put
together a virus that

00:30:48.180 --> 00:30:50.880
could actually make "zombies."

00:30:50.880 --> 00:30:52.870
They're not zombies in
the narrow sense, where

00:30:52.870 --> 00:30:54.420
they died and then resurrected.

00:30:54.420 --> 00:30:57.470
Because, frankly,
that doesn't work.

00:30:57.470 --> 00:30:59.450
You can write horror
or fantasy about those.

00:30:59.450 --> 00:31:00.910
But you can't really
do science fiction

00:31:00.910 --> 00:31:03.493
unless they're being controlled
by nanobots or something other

00:31:03.493 --> 00:31:06.020
than the body itself.

00:31:06.020 --> 00:31:08.280
And I wanted to do
science fiction.

00:31:08.280 --> 00:31:09.970
So it's like, OK.

00:31:09.970 --> 00:31:12.447
If I gave them all rabies,
would they be zombies?

00:31:12.447 --> 00:31:14.280
