00:39:28.080 --> 00:39:31.490
I find the hygiene hypothesis
extremely compelling.

00:39:31.490 --> 00:39:33.580
The hygiene hypothesis
holds that the reason

00:39:33.580 --> 00:39:36.360
for the rise in allergies
and autoimmune disorders

00:39:36.360 --> 00:39:39.980
among the population is because
for literally millennia,

00:39:39.980 --> 00:39:44.690
humans lived alongside with,
and affected by, parasites.

00:39:44.690 --> 00:39:46.840
Almost everyone would
have a parasitic infection

00:39:46.840 --> 00:39:49.170
at some point in their
lives, possibly more.

00:39:49.170 --> 00:39:51.590
Sometimes they'd just have
systemic parasitic infections

00:39:51.590 --> 00:39:52.950
for their entire lives.

00:39:52.950 --> 00:39:54.890
And they didn't have
very many allergies.

00:39:54.890 --> 00:39:57.360
And they didn't have very
many autoimmune disorders.

00:39:57.360 --> 00:40:03.470
These are all relatively recent
developments as far as "human"

00:40:03.470 --> 00:40:05.480
goes.

00:40:05.480 --> 00:40:07.430
What the hygiene
hypothesis holds

00:40:07.430 --> 00:40:11.150
is that our immune systems
evolved to be hypervigilant,

00:40:11.150 --> 00:40:13.360
so that they could fight
against those parasites

00:40:13.360 --> 00:40:15.120
and keep them from killing us.

00:40:15.120 --> 00:40:18.070
So an immune system, in
the absence of a parasite,

00:40:18.070 --> 00:40:21.020
is sort of like a five-year-old
boy with a baseball bat,

00:40:21.020 --> 00:40:23.270
