off, which you commented
on, and threatened

00:52:57.190 --> 00:52:58.190
to collaborate with her.

00:52:58.190 --> 00:52:59.969
Which, sign me up
for preorders now.

00:52:59.969 --> 00:53:02.010
But I'd love to hear you
talk about-- she started

00:53:02.010 --> 00:53:04.680
to talk about-- this character,
I put him in there to get

00:53:04.680 --> 00:53:06.560
killed off for
reasons X, Y, and Z.

00:53:06.560 --> 00:53:06.693
MIRA GRANT: Yeah.

00:53:06.693 --> 00:53:07.360
I tried that.

00:53:07.360 --> 00:53:08.680
I tried that once.

00:53:08.680 --> 00:53:11.060
I had this character who was
completely intended to die.

00:53:11.060 --> 00:53:12.660
Like their whole
purpose was to die.

00:53:12.660 --> 00:53:14.743
Every one talked about how
they were going to die.

00:53:14.743 --> 00:53:16.290
They didn't die.

00:53:16.290 --> 00:53:17.600
Their best friend dies.

00:53:17.600 --> 00:53:18.960
I was a little startled by that.

00:53:18.960 --> 00:53:21.440
I'm like wait,
what just happened?

00:53:21.440 --> 00:53:24.227
My subconscious lies to me
a lot, like a lot, a lot.

00:53:24.227 --> 00:53:26.060
Because it's the only
way that I will embark

00:53:26.060 --> 00:53:28.110
on these 10-book series
without going nope,

00:53:28.110 --> 00:53:30.590
I've got too much TV to watch.

00:53:30.590 --> 00:53:32.861
So I will frequently
find myself getting to,

00:53:32.861 --> 00:53:34.860
like, I'm 2/3 of the way
through with this book.

00:53:34.860 --> 00:53:35.610
It's great.

00:53:35.610 --> 00:53:38.070
I'm going to be
with the duo-- ah,

00:53:38.070 --> 00:53:41.945
the ending is still
like 180,000 words away.

00:53:41.945 --> 00:53:46.200
Has this been a
trilogy all along?

00:53:46.200 --> 00:53:49.110
Because I don't let myself
understand the scope

00:53:49.110 --> 00:53:50.822
of what I'm embarking on.

